{
    "id": "328",
    "title": "Systematic Coronary Risk Evaluation 2-Older Persons (SCORE2-OP)",
    "desc": "SCORE2-Older Persons (SCORE2-OP) predicts 10-year CVD risk in older patients.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34120185/",
                "text": "SCORE2-OP working group and ESC Cardiovascular risk collaboration. SCORE2-OP risk prediction algorithms: estimating incident cardiovascular event risk in older persons in four geographical risk regions. Eur Heart J. 2021;42(25):2455-2467."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The model coefficients, baseline survival, and mean linear predictor to calculate 10-year risk of CVD are as follows:</span><b></b></p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\">\n<table style=\"width: 99.8773%;\"><colgroup><col width=\"102\" style=\"width: 27.2413%;\"><col width=\"143\" style=\"width: 36.7808%;\"><col width=\"104\" style=\"width: 17.9066%;\"><col width=\"99\" style=\"width: 17.9066%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Risk Factor</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Transformation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Male</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Female</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Age, years</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>cage = age &ndash; 73</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0634</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0789</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Diabetes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>yes = 1, no = 0</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.4245</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.6010</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Smoking</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>current = 1, other = 0</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.3524</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.4921</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>SBP, mm Hg</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>csbp = sbp &ndash; 150</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0094</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0102</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Total cholesterol, mmol/L</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>ctchol = tchol &ndash; 6</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0850</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0605</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HDL cholesterol, mmol/L</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>chdl = hdl &ndash; 1.4</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.3564</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.3040</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Diabetes*age interaction</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>diabetes*cage</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0174</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0107</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Smoking*age interaction</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>smoking*cage</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0247</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0255</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>SBP*age interaction</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>csbp*cage</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0005</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0004</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Total cholesterol*age interaction</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>ctchol*cage</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0073</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.0009</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HDL cholesterol*age interaction</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>chdl*cage</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0091</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.0154</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Baseline survival</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>0.7576</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>0.8082</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Mean linear predictor (MLP)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>0.0929</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>0.2290</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The 10-year risk of CVD is calculated by the following:</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>10-year risk</strong> = 1 &ndash; (baseline survival)</span><sup><span>exp(x &ndash; MLP)</span></sup><span>,</span><b></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>where <strong>x</strong> = &Sigma;[&beta;*(transformed variables)]</span><b></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The region and sex-specific scales to calculate calibrated 10-year risk are as follows:</span><b></b></p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\">\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"114\"><col width=\"85\"><col width=\"86\"><col width=\"84\"><col width=\"76\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Male</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Female</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Risk Region</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Scale 1</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Scale 2</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Scale 1</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Scale 2</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Low</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.34</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.19</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.52</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.01</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Moderate</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.01</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.25</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-0.10</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.10</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>High</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.08</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.15</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.38</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.09</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Very high</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.05</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.70</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.38</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0.69</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The calibrated 10-year risk of CVD is calculated by the following:</span><b></b></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Calibrated 10-year risk, %</strong> = [1 &ndash; exp(-exp(scale1 + scale2*ln(-ln(1 &ndash; 10-year risk))))]*100</span></p>",
        "facts": "<p>Risk regions are defined by the following map:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/score2.png\" width=\"100%\"></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>From </span><a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34120185/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>SCORE2 Working Group 2021</span></a><span>.</span></p>",
